`transaction.find_datum(datums, datum_hash)` looks up a datum by its `DatumHash` in the transaction's `datums` map and returns `Option<Data>`. It is used when an output carries a datum hash reference rather than an inline datum. The validator retrieves the pre-image from the transaction's witness set via this helper.

```aiken
use cardano/transaction

validator hash_datum_check {
  spend(_datum, _redeemer, own_ref, self) {
    let own_input = transaction.resolve_input(self.inputs, own_ref)
    // If the output uses a datum hash, look it up in self.datums
    expect Some(hash) = own_input.output.datum
    let found = transaction.find_datum(self.datums, hash)
    Some(found) != None
  }
}
```

