The wrong pattern:

```aiken
// WRONG: grabs an arbitrary first input instead of the governed UTxO
expect Some(first) = list.head(self.inputs)
let val = first.output.value
```

The correct approach in Aiken v3 resolves the validator's own reference:

```aiken
use cardano/transaction

validator safe_own_input {
  spend(_datum, _redeemer, own_ref, self) {
    let own_input = transaction.resolve_input(self.inputs, own_ref)
    // use own_input.output.value safely
    True
  }
}
```

`list.head` returns whichever input happens to be first after sorting — that is never guaranteed to be the script's UTxO.

